summary: The Importance of Taylor
title: The Importance of Taylor
body:
The Importance of Taylor:



A tribute to the healing and saving powers that Taylor’s music, and all around words give to her fans. A couple months before the 1989 tour I lost me Dad, Taylors speech before clean gave me a new sight into life. There have been so many other examples of Taylor pushing me through days I may not have gotten through with her messages, her quotes, and her songs. I would love to thank her, not only just for her art, but for giving me back my perspective on life and my personal worth.



If I could meet Taylor,

What enchantment I’d feel,

The darkness I have been under,

For the last 4 years would cease to be still,

I would explain every reason as how she saved me night after night

And thank her forever,

For being that beacon of light,

I would stand there in moment,

In a dream come true daze,

Cause it is not on the regular,

You meet your heroes these days,

I would let her know truly ,

That her art changes life,

That it takes fans by the hand,

And chases away strife.

I know there will be smiles,

And at least a few tears,

a lot of confusion,

But I hope that what most appears,

Is my true admiration for the craft that she gives,

The songs that have taken me away from darkness,

Given me the imagination to live,

That even through losing so many so soon,

The sorrow can be lifted,

With her hand written tunes,

How she has taught me self love,

Is what reputation is,

And that bullies have no ownership,

Over my vibrancy and fizz,

That names may be posted,

And my character attacked,

But through all of these challenges,

I can come fighting back,

Cause if Taylor can keep on,

I know I can to,

Life is a hurdle,

But I guess I got some more to jump through,

And as long as I have Taylor,

Track by Track there for me,

There is never a obstacle,

That can stop,

Or cause this fighter to flee,

So I hope more then ever,

I can tell her to her face,

I kind of example,

that her presence has left of this earthly place,

Because she contains power,

To help other souls dream,

And I for one know,

Because she was that example for me,

So I hope that she reads this,

And that it to warms her heart,

Cause I am forever a Swiftie,

Because Swift saved and gave to this fan a new start.

By. Dustin Atwood

summary: I might be getting a bit sentimental now that my concert is just around the corner and some might say i'm saying these things...
body: I might be getting a bit sentimental now that my concert is just around the corner and some might say i’m saying these things only because of that,but let me tell you this,never in million years did i think that i will have a chance to see Taylor. I come from a very small europien country which Taylor has never been to. Never did i thought that i will move to Ireland. When i moved here 3 years ago Taylor was here on her 1989 tour,but since i moved like 3 days before that i couldn’t go to the show. I was so heartbroken,i have never been in the same country as her. I cried for about 2 days. Then Taylor took a break and i said to myself whenever she comes back i’ll be ready. I saved money and kept dreaming about the day it will finally happen. And here we are two days before my very first show. If you could see me now you could tell what a mess i am. @taylorswift i have never felt so happy in my life. Never. I love you so so soooo much.
